-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Sept 9
-- 
-- Tue Sep 09, 2014 03:22AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Sept 9 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Tuesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Bulgaria has decided to increase its armed forces by 2,500 people to 26,000 for the first time since 1989, the interim government decided at a closed meeting last week. (24 Chasa, Presa, Trud) -- Centre-right GERB party is sending all of its candidates for a seat in parliament to help in the areas hit by devastating floods, the party said. (Presa, 24 Chasa, Sega)